    <script>
        // CS:S style interactions
        document.querySelectorAll('.player-card').forEach(card => {
            card.addEventListener('mouseenter', function() {
                // Add CS weapon pickup sound effect simulation
                this.style.transform = 'translateY(-3px)';
                this.style.boxShadow = '0 10px 25px rgba(255, 140, 0, 0.4), inset 0 0 15px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.7)';
            });
            
            card.addEventListener('mouseleave', function() {
                this.style.transform = 'translateY(0)';
                this.style.boxShadow = 'inset 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5)';
            });
        });
        
        // Simulate CS console loading
        const title = document.querySelector('.title');
        const originalText = title.textContent;
        title.textContent = '';
        
        function consoleType(text, element, speed = 150) {
            let i = 0;
            function type() {
                if (i < text.length) {
                    element.textContent += text.charAt(i);
                    i++;
                    setTimeout(type, speed);
                }
            }
            type();
        }
        
        setTimeout(() => {
            consoleType(originalText, title, 120);
        }, 500);
        
        // Simulate round timer
        let roundTime = 300; // 5 minutes
        function updateRoundInfo() {
            const roundInfo = document.querySelector('.round-info');
            const minutes = Math.floor(roundTime / 60);
            const seconds = roundTime % 60;
            roundInfo.innerHTML = `Map: de_bachelor | Time: ${minutes}:${seconds.toString().padStart(2, '0')} | Players: 6/32`;
            if (roundTime > 0) {
                roundTime--;
                setTimeout(updateRoundInfo, 1000);
            }
        }
        
        setTimeout(updateRoundInfo, 3000);
    </script>

        // CS:S style interactions
        document.querySelectorAll('.player-card').forEach(card => {
            card.addEventListener('mouseenter', function() {
                // Add CS weapon pickup sound effect simulation
                this.style.transform = 'translateY(-3px)';
                this.style.boxShadow = '0 10px 25px rgba(255, 140, 0, 0.4), inset 0 0 15px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.7)';
            });
            
            card.addEventListener('mouseleave', function() {
                this.style.transform = 'translateY(0)';
                this.style.boxShadow = 'inset 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5)';
            });
        });
        
        // Simulate CS console loading
        const title = document.querySelector('.title');
        const originalText = title.textContent;
        title.textContent = '';
        
        function consoleType(text, element, speed = 150) {
            let i = 0;
            function type() {
                if (i < text.length) {
                    element.textContent += text.charAt(i);
                    i++;
                    setTimeout(type, speed);
                }
            }
            type();
        }
        
        setTimeout(() => {
            consoleType(originalText, title, 120);
        }, 500);
        
        // Simulate round timer
        let roundTime = 300; // 5 minutes
        function updateRoundInfo() {
            const roundInfo = document.querySelector('.round-info');
            const minutes = Math.floor(roundTime / 60);
            const seconds = roundTime % 60;
            roundInfo.innerHTML = `Map: de_bachelor | Time: ${minutes}:${seconds.toString().padStart(2, '0')} | Players: 6/32`;
            if (roundTime > 0) {
                roundTime--;
                setTimeout(updateRoundInfo, 1000);
            }
        }
        
        setTimeout(updateRoundInfo, 3000);
    </script>

how to host this website for free

There are several ways to host this website for free! Here are a few popular options:

  1. GitHub Pages: If your website is primarily static HTML, CSS, and JavaScript (like the one I've created), GitHub Pages is an excellent free option. You just push your code to a GitHub repository, and it can be hosted directly from there.

  2. Netlify: Netlify offers a very generous free tier for static sites. You can connect it to your GitHub repository, and it will automatically build and deploy your site whenever you push changes. It also provides features like custom domains and HTTPS.

  3. Vercel: Similar to Netlify, Vercel is another popular platform for deploying static sites and front-end applications. It also integrates well with GitHub and offers a free tier.

  4. Firebase Hosting: If you plan to add more dynamic features or a backend later, Firebase Hosting (part of Google Firebase) offers free hosting for static content, and it integrates well with other Firebase services.

For a simple static site like this, GitHub Pages or Netlify would likely be the easiest and quickest to get started with!
